  "text": "In AML, pediatric regimens tend to be comprised of several courses of multi-agent chemotherapy, whereas adult regimens generally treat with single-agent cytarabine after the first induction cycle. Hematopoietic stem cell transplantation is offered to a higher proportion of adult AML patients. There are many fewer retrospective studies in AML comparing outcomes for AYA patients treated on pediatric vs. adult protocols, and the results are mixed, with some showing a benefit for pediatric protocols and others showing no difference [CITATION_1] .",
